        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 5:57PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Avondale to near Fowler. Movement was east at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sugar City, Rocky Ford, Ordway, Swink, Fowler, Boone, Olney Springs,
Crowley, Manzanola, Timpas, North La Junta, La Junta, and Avondale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
